Azimio la Umoja One Kenya presidential aspirant Raila Odinga will take his campaigns to Bungoma county on Saturday. Raila who will be accompanied by Azimio leaders will go through St. Luke’s Kimilili Boys High School. At the school, Raila and the leaders will open the Multi-purpose hall then later head to a funeral service of Burudi Nabwera’s wife at Sango Farm in Kiminini (Transnzoia County). He will then head to Tongareni constituency and make stop overs in Brigdia market, Ndalu market and Naitiri market. Raila is also expected at Webuye East constituency. He will make stop overs at Nzoia ,Lurare dispensary (Maraka ward) at 2:30pm. By 4pm, he will be expected at Lukusi market before going to Sitikho ward_milo market at  5pm in Webuye West. Raila is seeking to galvanize the support of voters in Bungoma County to boost his bid in the region. DP William Ruto on the other hand will be expected  in Nyandarua, Narok and Nakuru Counties on Saturday. Ruto will make stop overs at Mùrùngarù, Kinangop Constituency. By 11 am, Ruto will be at William ole Ntimama Stadium, Narok North Constituency. He will then head to Maela in Naivasha constituency at 3pm.